{"ticketId":"42","phase":"planning","id":"42-74","detail":"---\n\n## Planner Report: Issue #42 ã Glossary (`docs\/GLOSSARY.md`)\n\n### 1. Project Ground Truth\n\n**Language \/ framework:** TypeScript (SvelteKit frontend `apps\/web`, SAM\/Node.js Lambda backend in `infra\/functions`). The glossary is a **docs-only change** ã no code.\n\n**Where the terms are defined in code** (for accurate glossary prose):\n\n| Term | Source of truth | Key file(s) |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Provider** | `ProviderDefinition` type + `DEFAULT_PROVIDERS` array | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:163ã170`, `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/providers.ts:3ã56` |\n| **Provider ID** | The `id` field on `ProviderDefinition` ã 26 stable kebab-case slugs (e.g. `aws-polly`, `elevenlabs`, `gcp-tts`) | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/providers.ts:3` (list), `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:164` |\n| **Voice** | `Voice` type ã catalog entity with id, name, provider, languages, variants, samples, metadata, modelCard | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:117ã154` |\n| **Dialect** | Not a code-level type ã conceptual. Vokda normalizes each provider's native API shape into a common request\/response shape (the `SynthesisRequest` \/ `SynthesisPreview` types vs. provider-specific adapters). The adapter pattern embodies this. | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/synthesis\/types.ts:3ã25` (SynthesisRequest), `infra\/functions\/synthesis-router\/lib\/adapters\/` (adapter dir) |\n| **Catalog** | The JSON dataset of voices + the code that loads\/aggregates it. Loaded from `\/data\/voices.json` (550 voices across 25 providers). Aggregation layer in `provider-catalog.ts`. | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/catalog.ts`, `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/provider-catalog.ts`, `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:117` (Voice type) |\n| **Capability** | `VoiceVariant` fields: `supportsSsml`, `outputFormats`, `maxInputChars`, `runnable`, `previewOnly`. Also `ProviderCatalogEntry` aggregates (ssmlSupport, languageCount, etc.). | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:5ã13` (VoiceVariant), `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/provider-catalog.ts:11ã29` (ProviderCatalogEntry) |\n| **Job** | `SynthesisJob` type ã `id`, `voiceId`, `inputText`, `inputMode` (`text`|`ssml`), `status` (`pending`|`completed`|`failed`), `audioUrl`, `provider`, etc. | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:222ã233` |\n| **SSML tag** | `SsmlTagDef` type ã `tag`, `label`, `description`, `category`, `selfClosing`, `attributes`, `providers` (compatibility matrix). 7 core tags defined. | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/ssml\/tags.ts:8ã18` (SsmlTagDef), `:46ã310` (SSML_TAGS array) |\n| **Steering** | `ProviderSteering` type ã `kind` (`instructions`|`styles`|`settings`|`none`), `label`, `placeholder`, `options`, `settings`, `audioTags`. Resolved per-voice by `getProviderSteering()`. | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/synthesis\/provider-steering.ts:20ã33` (ProviderSteering), `:46ã90` (resolver) |\n\n### 2. Existing Docs Landscape\n\nThe `docs\/` directory contains 15 files:\n\n```\nAMPLIFY_BACKEND_GEN2.md  AMPLIFY_SETUP.md  API.md  ARCHITECTURE.md\nDISCOVERY.md  GITHUB_SETUP.md  ROADMAP.md  SCHEMA.md  SYNTHESIS_API.md\nVISION.md  VOICE_CATALOG_EXPORT.md  voice-discovery-process.md\nconstitutions\/  research\/  specs\/\n```\n\n- **No `GLOSSARY.md` exists.**\n- **No `PROVIDER_IDS.md` exists** (the glossary's cross-link target is forward-looking).\n- **No standalone SSML docs file exists.** SSML documentation lives in `docs\/DISCOVERY.md` (the \"SSML Editor\" section, starting at ~line 110) and `specs\/feat-ssml-editor.md`.\n\n### 3. Linking Point\n\n**`README.md`** (repo root) has a \"Product Docs\" list at line ~53:\n\n```markdown\n## Product Docs\n- Product requirements: `PRD.md`\n- Architecture baseline: `docs\/ARCHITECTURE.md`\n- Delivery plan: `docs\/ROADMAP.md`\n- API baseline: `docs\/API.md`\n- Data model baseline: `docs\/SCHEMA.md`\n- Amplify backend setup: `docs\/AMPLIFY_BACKEND_GEN2.md`\n```\n\nA one-line pointer like `- Glossary: `docs\/GLOSSARY.md`` should be added here.\n\n### 4. Cross-Link Targets (Resolved)\n\n| Glossary term | Cross-link target | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Provider ID** | `docs\/PROVIDER_IDS.md` | **Does not exist** ã forward-looking link; the glossary should still reference it. The canonical list of provider IDs lives in `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/providers.ts` (26 entries). |\n| **SSML tag** | SSML docs | **No standalone SSML doc exists.** Best available target: `docs\/DISCOVERY.md#ssml-editor` (the SSML Editor section) or `specs\/feat-ssml-editor.md`. Recommend linking to the DISCOVERY.md section. |\n\n### 5. Job Status Enum\n\nThe `SynthesisJob.status` field uses exactly: `'pending' | 'completed' | 'failed'`. This is the canonical lifecycle. Defined at `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:227`.\n\n### 6. What the Glossary Should Look Like (shape only ã NOT writing it)\n\n- **Format:** Markdown, in `docs\/GLOSSARY.md`.\n- **Tone:** Descriptive, integrator-facing, 1ã3 sentences per term. No code blocks required.\n- **Terms to define (from the AC):** Provider, Provider ID, Voice, Dialect, Catalog, Capability, Job, SSML tag, Steering.\n- **Cross-links needed:**\n  - Provider ID ã `[provider ID](PROVIDER_IDS.md)`\n  - SSML tag ã `[SSML Editor](DISCOVERY.md#ssml-editor)` (or `specs\/feat-ssml-editor.md`)\n- **README addition:** One line in the Product Docs list.\n\n### 7. Boundaries\n\n- **Out of scope:** Code changes of any kind. No per-provider tables. No API reference content (that's `SYNTHESIS_API.md` and `API.md`). No normative\/spec-level definitions (that's `SCHEMA.md`).\n- **Glossary is descriptive only** ã it explains what the terms mean, not how to use them programmatically.","outcome":{"note":{}},"at":804555592.333271}
