{"phase":"decompose","at":804556049.296721,"id":"42-124","outcome":{"note":{}},"ticketId":"42","detail":"---\n\n## Decomposer Report for #42: docs: add a glossary of core API terms (`docs\/GLOSSARY.md`)\n\n### Project & Stack\n\n- **Vokda** ã voice discovery and curation app (\"Pinterest for TTS voices\"), 550 voices across 25 providers, 53 languages.\n- **Stack**: SvelteKit 4 (TypeScript) frontend, AWS Amplify Gen2 (Cognito + AppSync\/DynamoDB), SAM-deployed Synthesis API (9 provider adapters). Monorepo: `apps\/web`, `apps\/api`, `packages\/sdk`, `packages\/shared`, `infra`.\n- **Docs dir**: 11 files (API.md, SYNTHESIS_API.md, DISCOVERY.md, SCHEMA.md, ARCHITECTURE.md, VISION.md, ROADMAP.md, AMPLIFY_BACKEND_GEN2.md, AMPLIFY_SETUP.md, GITHUB_SETUP.md, VOICE_CATALOG_EXPORT.md) + `constitutions\/`, `research\/`, `specs\/`.\n- **README.md** has a \"Product Docs\" bullet list ã the link insertion point.\n\n### What Already Exists (ground-truth)\n\n| Fact | Source |\n|------|--------|\n| 9 target terms are well-established in the codebase and existing docs | `docs\/SCHEMA.md`, `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md`, `docs\/DISCOVERY.md`, `CLAUDE.md` |\n| **Provider** model: 25 providers in catalog, 9 with server-side adapters. Defined as `providerId` slug + display name. | `docs\/SCHEMA.md` (ProviderRecord), `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md` ôÏ Supported Providers |\n| **Provider ID** slugs: e.g. `openai`, `aws-polly`, `azure-speech`, `elevenlabs`, `gcp-tts`, `deepgram`, `cartesia`, `lmnt`, `gemini-tts`, `edge-tts` | `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md` ôÏ Supported Providers |\n| **Voice**: 550 voices, each with `id` (ULID), `name`, `providerId`, `providerVoiceId`, variants, samples, modelCard, steering | `docs\/SCHEMA.md` ôÏ Voice |\n| **Dialect**: adapter pattern ã each Synthesis API adapter normalizes the Vokda request\/response shape to\/from the provider's native API shape | `CLAUDE.md` ôÏ synthesis\/adapters\/, `infra\/functions\/synthesis-router\/lib\/adapters\/` |\n| **Catalog**: `apps\/web\/static\/data\/voices.json` (source of truth), served via `\/api\/v1\/voices.json`, `\/api\/v1\/providers.json`, `\/api\/v1\/openapi.json` | `docs\/SCHEMA.md` ôÏ Catalog Models, `docs\/API.md` |\n| **Capability**: per-provider feature flags ã `ssmlSupport`, `supportsStreaming`, `maxTextLength`, `outputFormats`; surfaced in `\/v1\/providers` and `\/v1\/voices` | `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md` ôÏ Voice capabilities, recall_shadow #24 |\n| **Job** (SynthesisJob): `pending | completed | failed`; stored in DynamoDB with `voiceId`, `providerId`, `inputText`, `inputMode`, `audioPath`, `durationMs`, `waveformJson`, etc. | `docs\/SCHEMA.md` ôÏ SynthesisJob, `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md` ôÏ GET\/PATCH\/DELETE \/v1\/jobs |\n| **SSML tag**: 7 tags ã `break`, `emphasis`, `prosody`, `say-as`, `phoneme`, `sub`, `lang` ã with per-provider support matrix (aws-polly, azure-speech, gcp-tts, edge-tts) | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/ssml\/tags.ts`, `docs\/DISCOVERY.md` ôÏ SSML Editor |\n| **Steering**: expressivity control per voice ã `kind`: `instructions` (OpenAI), `styles` (AWS Polly newscaster), `settings` (ElevenLabs), `none` (all others) | `docs\/SCHEMA.md` ôÏ Steering, `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md` ôÏ Voice capabilities |\n| `docs\/PROVIDER_IDS.md` **does NOT exist** | `list_files docs` ã absent |\n| No separate SSML doc ã SSML content lives in `docs\/DISCOVERY.md#ssml-editor` (editor guide, quick reference) and `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md` (API examples) | both files scanned |\n| README.md ôÏ \"Product Docs\" has 6 bullet entries ã the glossary link goes here | `README.md` lines 35ã40 |\n\n### Deliverables (independently buildable)\n\n| # | Deliverable | Description | Dependencies |\n|---|-------------|-------------|-------------|\n| **D1** | Create `docs\/GLOSSARY.md` | Write the 9 term definitions (1ã3 sentences each), integrator-focused prose, with cross-links to `docs\/PROVIDER_IDS.md` and `docs\/DISCOVERY.md#ssml-editor`. Pure docs ã no code. | None |\n| **D2** | Link from README.md | Add one bullet `- Glossary: docs\/GLOSSARY.md` under \"Product Docs\" in `README.md`. | D1 |\n\n### Cross-link facts\n\n- **\"cross-link to `docs\/PROVIDER_IDS.md`\"** ã This file **does not exist yet**. The glossary should still reference it per the issue's instruction. Existing provider ID info is at `docs\/SYNTHESIS_API.md#supported-providers`.\n- **\"cross-link to the SSML docs\"** ã The project has no standalone SSML doc. The authoritative SSML documentation is `docs\/DISCOVERY.md#ssml-editor` (tag toolbar, validation, quick reference, provider matrix). Use that as the cross-link target.\n\n### Out of scope (confirmed)\n\n- No code changes ã purely a new `docs\/GLOSSARY.md` + one-line README edit.\n- No exhaustive per-provider tables (the catalog already has those).\n\n---\n\n**Ready for next phase.** The two deliverables are trivial, sequential, and entirely self-contained in the `docs\/` directory and `README.md`. D1 can be authored directly; D2 is a one-line insertion."}
